dashboard.definition:
{
	"title": "Advanced Masking of Data with SHA1",
	"description": "",
	"inputs": {},
	"defaults": {
		"dataSources": {
			"ds.search": {
				"options": {
					"queryParameters": {}
				}
			},
			"ds.spl2": {
				"options": {
					"queryParameters": {}
				}
			}
		},
		"visualizations": {
			"global": {
				"showProgressBar": true
			}
		}
	},
	"visualizations": {
		"viz_markdown": {
			"type": "splunk.markdown",
			"options": {
				"markdown": "# Problem description\n\nSome data contains private or secret information like user names and passwords that it is inappropiate for all eyes to see. Under these circumstances data needs to be hidden from those users, for instance 1st line support. However this we may still need to keep the orginal data for other reasons, for higher security level users. Splunk doesn't allow for selective masking at point of search, which is a significant challenge for any unstructured data system.\n\n## Existing Solutions\nSplunk documentation a section on how to [Anonymize data|https://docs.splunk.com/Documentation/Splunk/8.0.6/Data/Anonymizedata]. However this is destructive to the orignal event and the ability to see the orginal event is lost. \n\n\n## Proposed Solution\nThis problem has been addressed in the example [mask and map|mask_and_map], this solution works but it results in double ingestion costs and the semi masking of email addresses isn't great. This solution also uses `CLONE_SOURCETYPE` to create another version of the event, but in this instance we will use a hashing algorithm to encode both the user and the password. The cloned event will have indexed fields to hold a map to undo the map. We can then combine the events to undo the map effeciently at search time. This approach allows for some cool functionality that could not be implemented with a lookup.\n\n###  Example log line\n\n    23:16:25 20-09-23 my email_address=julian@wikileaks.com and my terrible password=\"onetimepassword\"\n\n### The steps performed to process data\n\n1. We intercept the data under the `mask_data_and_map` sourcetype, before we clone the event we need to do some work\n   1. Extract the email address using a regex transform and store the email address as an indexed field\n   2. Extract the password using a regex transform and store the password as an indexed field \n2. We create encoded versions of the indexed fields for password and email address\n   1. We compute the hash on the email field but only keep the first 10 charactors so that the event doesn't become excessively long `substr(sha1(email_address),0,10)` \n   2. We compute the hash of the password AND email field, this means that it is not possible to search for users using the same password, i.e. the hash is scoped the email address. Yet we are able to see if the user has changed their password\n3. We clone the event ...\n   1. ... with the original \n      1. We update the `_raw` string using the `replace` function to swap the unencoded values with the new encoded ones\n      2. We remove the encoded and unencoded indexed fields \n   2. ... with the cloned event \n      1. We replace the `_raw` string with a single charactor to reduce licensing\n      2. We keep the indexed fields which become the translation\n\nWhen we search the event we are able to efficently match the encoded log line and the mapping because they appear at the same moment in time.\n\n    index=ingest_eval_examples* sourcetype=mask_data_and_map-map OR sourcetype=mask_data_and_map\n    | stats values(eval(if(_raw!=\".\",_raw,NULL))) as _raw \n        values(password_decoded) as password_decoded\n        values(email_address_decoded) as email_address_decoded\n        by _time password email_address\n    | table _time _raw email_address_decoded password_decoded\n"
			}
		},
		"viz_anon": {
			"type": "splunk.table",
			"dataSources": {
				"primary": "ds_anon"
			},
			"options": {
				"drilldown": "none"
			},
			"showProgressBar": true,
			"title": "Annoymised data that is visable to all users"
		},
		"viz_map": {
			"type": "splunk.table",
			"dataSources": {
				"primary": "ds_map"
			},
			"options": {
				"drilldown": "none"
			},
			"showProgressBar": true,
			"title": "The translation table is visable to security users"
		},
		"viz_undo": {
			"type": "splunk.table",
			"dataSources": {
				"primary": "ds_undo"
			},
			"options": {
				"drilldown": "none"
			},
			"showProgressBar": true,
			"title": "We can join these two indexes together on time, password and user_name to reverse the map"
		},
		"viz_conf_props": {
			"type": "splunk.markdown",
			"options": {
				"markdown": "### props.conf\n\nFrom `default/props.conf` \u2014 verbatim:\n\n```ini\n[mask_data_and_map]\nTIME_PREFIX = ^\nTIME_FORMAT = %H:%M:%S %y-%m-%d\nSHOULD_LINEMERGE=false\nLINE_BREAKER=([\\n\\r]+)\nTRANSFORMS-apply-masking=mask_data_and_map-extract_email, mask_data_and_map-extract_password, mask_data_and_map-encode_email_and_password, mask_data_and_map-clone, mask_data_and_map-apply_hashes\n\n[mask_data_and_map-clone]\nTRANSFORMS-create_map = shared-route_to_ingest_eval_examples_2, mask_data_and_map-create_map\nrename=mask_data_and_map-map\n```\n"
			}
		},
		"viz_conf_transforms": {
			"type": "splunk.markdown",
			"options": {
				"markdown": "### transforms.conf\n\nFrom `default/transforms.conf` \u2014 verbatim:\n\n```ini\n[mask_data_and_map-extract_password]\nSOURCE_KEY = _raw\nWRITE_META = true\nREGEX = password=\"(.*)\"$\nFORMAT = password::\"$1\"\n\n[mask_data_and_map-extract_email]\nSOURCE_KEY = _raw\nWRITE_META = true\nREGEX = email_address=(\\S+@\\S+)\nFORMAT = email_address::\"$1\"\n\n[mask_data_and_map-clone]\nSOURCE_KEY = MetaData:Host\nDEST_KEY = MetaData:Host\nREGEX = (.)\nFORMAT = %0\nCLONE_SOURCETYPE = mask_data_and_map-clone\n\n[mask_data_and_map-encode_email_and_password]\nINGEST_EVAL =  email_address_encoded=substr(sha1(email_address),0,10), password_encoded=substr(sha1(email_address.password),0,10)\n\n[mask_data_and_map-apply_hashes]\nINGEST_EVAL = _raw=replace(_raw, \"email_address=\\S+\", \"email_address=\".email_address_encoded), _raw=replace(_raw, \"password=\\\".*\\\"$\",\"password=\\\"\".password_encoded.\"\\\"\"), email_address:=null(), password :=null(), password_encoded:=null(), email_address_encoded:=null()\n\n[mask_data_and_map-create_map]\nINGEST_EVAL = _raw=\".\", email_address_decoded:=email_address, email_address:=email_address_encoded, password_decoded:=password, password:=password_encoded, password_encoded:=null(), email_address_encoded:=null()\n```\n"
			}
		}
	},
	"dataSources": {
		"ds_anon": {
			"name": "Anonymised data",
			"type": "ds.search",
			"options": {
				"query": "index=ingest_eval_examples_* sourcetype=mask_data_and_map\n| table _raw",
				"queryParameters": {
					"earliest": "0",
					"latest": ""
				}
			}
		},
		"ds_map": {
			"name": "Translation table",
			"type": "ds.search",
			"options": {
				"query": "index=\"ingest_eval_examples_2\" sourcetype=mask_data_and_map-map \n| table _time email_address email_address_decoded password password_decoded",
				"queryParameters": {
					"earliest": "0",
					"latest": ""
				}
			}
		},
		"ds_undo": {
			"name": "Undo join",
			"type": "ds.search",
			"options": {
				"query": "index=ingest_eval_examples* sourcetype=mask_data_and_map-map OR sourcetype=mask_data_and_map\n| stats values(eval(if(_raw!=\".\",_raw,NULL))) as _raw \n    values(password_decoded) as password_decoded\n    values(email_address_decoded) as email_address_decoded\n    by _time password email_address\n| table _time _raw email_address_decoded password_decoded",
				"queryParameters": {
					"earliest": "0",
					"latest": ""
				}
			}
		}
	},
	"layout": {
		"globalInputs": [],
		"layoutDefinitions": {
			"layout_1": {
				"type": "grid",
				"options": {
					"width": 1440,
					"height": 250
				},
				"structure": [
					{
						"item": "viz_markdown",
						"type": "block",
						"position": {
							"x": 0,
							"y": 0,
							"w": 720,
							"h": 800
						}
					},
					{
						"item": "viz_anon",
						"type": "block",
						"position": {
							"x": 720,
							"y": 0,
							"w": 720,
							"h": 400
						}
					},
					{
						"item": "viz_map",
						"type": "block",
						"position": {
							"x": 720,
							"y": 400,
							"w": 720,
							"h": 400
						}
					},
					{
						"item": "viz_undo",
						"type": "block",
						"position": {
							"x": 0,
							"y": 800,
							"w": 1440,
							"h": 500
						}
					},
					{
						"item": "viz_conf_props",
						"type": "block",
						"position": {
							"x": 0,
							"y": 1300,
							"w": 720,
							"h": 480
						}
					},
					{
						"item": "viz_conf_transforms",
						"type": "block",
						"position": {
							"x": 720,
							"y": 1300,
							"w": 720,
							"h": 480
						}
					}
				]
			}
		},
		"options": {
			"submitButton": false
		},
		"tabs": {
			"items": [
				{
					"label": "New tab",
					"layoutId": "layout_1"
				}
			]
		}
	},
	"applicationProperties": {
		"hideEdit": false,
		"hideExport": false
	}
}
